          This operation terminates any previous set trigger, and
          set  a  new  trigger  specified by the _T_i_m_e_T_y_p_e and _U_T_O
          object.

          The relation between the UTO object and  the  TimeTypes
          are:

            * 'TTAbsolute' - the UTO object must represent  abso-
              lute  time,  i.e., number of 100 nanoseconds passed
              since 15 october 1582 00:00.

            * 'TTRelative' - the UTO object  must  represent  the
              from  now until when the event should be triggered,
              e.g., within 30*10^7 nanoseconds.

            * 'TTPeriodic' - the same as  for  'TTRelative',  but
              this  option  will  trigger  an  event periodically
              until timer cancelled.

